Kubernetes pods

1.How many pods exist on the system?
In the current(default) namespace.

There are no pods in the default namespace currently, so the correct answer is 0.

2.Create a new pod using the nginx image.
Run the command: kubectl run nginx --image=nginx

controlplane ~ ➜  kubectl run nginx --image=nginx
pod/nginx created

3.How many pods are created now?
Note: We have created a few more pods. So please check again in the current(default) namespace.

Run the command kubectl get pods and count the number of pods.

controlplane ~ ➜  kubectl get pods
